			</span>
			<a href="http://asymptomatic.net/2009/04/11/2800/why-am-i-still-awake#comment-263222" title="Link to this comment" itemprop="url">
				<time class="comment-date" datetime="2009-04-15 13:40:20" itemprop="dateCreated">
					Apr 15, 2009 1:40 pm				</time>
			</a>
		</h1>
	</header>
	<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text"><p>I used to find myself afflicted by a productivity-sapping brain fog during the day and couldn't figure out how to snap out of it.  Then I stopped (routinely anyway) working 'til 5am and getting up at 7:30am.  Getting old stinks.</p><p>I likewise find myself more productive late at night.  Although a big factor for me is the reduction in distraction from incoming phone calls, emails, and pterodactyls, which has less to do with brain science than with my work/life situations.</p></div>
</article>
